---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — SFCE Learning App for Android"
  description="Privacy policy for the SFCE Learning native app for Android."
  canonicalPath="/app/android/privacy-policy/"
  footerVariant="app"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary dark:text-dark-text-secondary mb-8">
      <strong class="text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary">Last updated:</strong> May 20, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-text-secondary dark:text-dark-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        SFCE Learning app ("the app", "we", "us") is a native study guide for the Symfony Framework
        Certification Exam. This Privacy Policy explains what information the app uses, where it is
        stored, and how privacy-related Android and Google Play services are used.
      </p>

      <p>
        SFCE Learning app is designed to provide its study guide structure and quiz content without
        requiring an account with us. Documentation links open external websites. The app does not
        use advertising, does not use analytics SDKs, and does not track you across apps or websites.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We do not collect, sell, rent, or share personal information for advertising or tracking.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">SFCE Learning app does not collect:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Your name, email address, phone number, or address</li>
          <li>Precise or coarse location</li>
          <li>Contacts, photos, camera, microphone, or health data</li>
          <li>Advertising identifiers (such as the Android Advertising ID)</li>
          <li>Analytics events or telemetry</li>
          <li>Crash reports sent to our own servers</li>
          <li>Browsing history from the in-app browser</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The app does not include third-party analytics, advertising SDKs, or social tracking SDKs.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Study Progress</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning app stores your study progress so the app can show completed references,
          progress indicators, and your last-read location.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">This information may include:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Symfony version selected for study progress</li>
          <li>Completed reference identifiers</li>
          <li>Completion timestamps stored locally by the app</li>
          <li>Last-read topic and chapter identifiers</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          This data is stored on your device using standard Android storage technologies such as a
          Room (SQLite) database and DataStore Preferences. It is used only to provide app
          functionality.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Cross-Device Backup</h2>
        <p>
          If you have Android Auto Backup enabled for the app on your device, your study progress may
          be backed up to your Google Drive backup account by the Android operating system. This
          allows your progress to be restored when you reinstall the app or set up a new device.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The backed-up data is limited to the app's local study progress (such as completion state
          by Symfony version and reference identifier) and lightweight app preferences. SFCE Learning
          app does not back up your name, email address, or other contact information.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Android Auto Backup is provided by Google and the Android platform. We do not operate a
          server for this data and do not have access to the contents of your Google Drive backup.
          You can manage app backup and Google Drive backup settings on your device in the system
          settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Calendar Integration</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning app can create study sessions in your calendar when you choose the "Add to
          Calendar" action.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          When you use this feature, the app hands off to your system Calendar app using a standard
          Android calendar intent. You confirm and save the event inside your Calendar app; SFCE
          Learning app does not need the runtime calendar permission and does not read your existing
          calendar entries. Calendar events suggested by SFCE Learning app may include:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>A study title based on the selected chapter or reference</li>
          <li>A suggested start and end time</li>
          <li>Reference links or notes when relevant</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SFCE Learning app uses this calendar hand-off only to pre-fill the events you choose to
          create. The app does not upload your calendar data to us.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Study Reminders</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning app can schedule local study reminders when you choose the "Add Reminder"
          action.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Reminders are delivered as local notifications scheduled on your device using the Android
          <code class="text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary">AlarmManager</code> and shown
          by the system <code class="text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary">NotificationManager</code>.
          On Android 13 and newer, the app asks for the system notification permission so it can
          display these reminders. Local reminders created by SFCE Learning app may include:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>A study reminder title based on the selected chapter or reference</li>
          <li>Notes or reference links when relevant</li>
          <li>A scheduled time that you choose</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Reminders are scheduled and stored locally on your device. SFCE Learning app does not
          upload reminder content to us, and reminders are not sent through any remote push
          notification service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">In-App Browser and External Reference Links</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning app includes reference links to external documentation and websites. When
          you open a reference link, the page may open in an Android Custom Tab (powered by your
          default browser, such as Chrome) or, when Custom Tabs are unavailable, in an in-app
          <code class="text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary">WebView</code>.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          External websites are not operated by SFCE Learning app. Those websites may receive
          standard web request information, such as your IP address, browser information, cookies,
          or other data depending on their own privacy practices. Their handling of data is governed
          by their own privacy policies.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SFCE Learning app does not collect or store your in-app browsing history.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Purchases</h2>
        <p>
          If the app offers a purchase, such as a quiz unlock, the purchase flow is handled by
          Google through Google Play using the Google Play Billing Library.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          SFCE Learning app may check Google Play-provided purchase entitlement status to unlock
          purchased functionality. We do not receive or store your payment card details or Google
          Play payment information.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Google's handling of purchase, billing, and Google Account information is governed by
          Google's own privacy policy and Google Play terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Content Ownership Notice</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning app includes original study content, including quiz questions, answer
          options, and related quiz material. This content is provided for personal study use within
          the app.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          You may not copy, scrape, reproduce, republish, redistribute, sell, or use the app's quiz
          question and answer database to create another product or dataset without written
          permission from the developer.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          This notice does not claim ownership of Symfony, PHP, public technical facts, official
          documentation, or general programming concepts. Some simple questions or answers may
          naturally resemble common technical explanations or publicly known facts. The restriction
          applies to the app's authored selection, wording, structure, and quiz database as a whole.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell your data. We do not share your data with advertisers or data brokers.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Data may be processed by Google and Android platform services when you use system features
          such as Android Auto Backup, the Calendar app, system notifications, Google Play Billing,
          Android Custom Tabs, <code class="text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary">WebView</code>,
          or Google Play. These services are provided by Google and the Android platform and are
          subject to Google's privacy practices.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
        <p>
          Study progress remains on your device unless you delete it, uninstall the app, clear the
          app's data through Android system settings, or sign out of the device.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Auto Backup data remains in your Google Drive backup account according to Android's backup
          behavior and your Google account settings. You can manage backups and remove the app's
          backup data from your Google account at any time.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Calendar events and reminders created with help from SFCE Learning app remain in your
          Calendar app or in your device's scheduled notifications until you edit, dismiss, or
          delete them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          SFCE Learning app is a professional study tool for developers preparing for a
          certification exam. The app is not directed to children and does not knowingly collect
          personal information from children.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy if the app's privacy practices change. When we make
          changes, we will update the "Last updated" date above.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary dark:text-dark-text-primary mb-3">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy questions, contact the developer through the support contact listed on the
          SFCE Learning app's Google Play store listing or the official project website.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
